📌 Docker Basics – GS-Level Understanding
1. Core Concept
Docker enables containerization: package code + dependencies + OS libraries in a portable image.
Advantages for Goldman Sachs-level systems:
Consistency: same container works in dev, staging, production
Isolation: prevents conflicts between services
Scalability: integrates with orchestration platforms (Kubernetes, ECS)
CI/CD Friendly: easy integration with pipelines
2. Key Concepts
Concept	Description
Image	Read-only template containing app + dependencies
Container	Running instance of an image
Dockerfile	Script to build an image
Volume	Persistent storage outside container
Network	Container communication (bridge, host, overlay)
3. Sample Dockerfile for Python Microservice
# Base image
FROM python:3.12-slim

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy requirements and install
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

# Copy application code
COPY . .

# Expose port and define entrypoint
EXPOSE 8000
CMD ["uvicorn", "main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]

GS-Level Notes:

Keep images slim for faster deployment
Use multi-stage builds for production images
Mount volumes for logs or persistent storage
